[10.525732, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mnginx-c95765fd4-hgghs\u001b[0m: Running, 1/1 container is up.                                                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mnginx-c95765fd4-q94wj\u001b[0m: Running, 1/1 container is up.                                                                                                                                       \r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mbroken-app-5bcbdf7c9f-nqxvm\u001b[0m: ImagePullBackOff, unable to pull the image.                                                                                                                   \r\n\r\nThe \u001b[1;36;40mbroken-app\u001b[0m pod is experiencing an issue with pulling its Docker image. This could be due to a typo in the image name, the image not existing in the specified registry, or authentication \r\nissues if the registry requires credentials.                                                                                                                                                  \r\n\r\n\u001b[1mNext step:\u001b[0m Check the image name and ensure it's correct, verify that the image exists in the repository, and confirm any necessary authentication is configured.                              \r\n"]
