[23.678464, "o", "The \u001b[1;36;40mbroken-app\u001b[0m pod is in the \u001b[1;36;40mPending\u001b[0m state with a \u001b[1;36;40mContainersReady\u001b[0m condition of \u001b[1;36;40mFalse\u001b[0m. The specific reason provided is \u001b[1;36;40mImagePullBackOff\u001b[0m, which indicates that Kubernetes is unable to pull the \r\nspecified container image.                                                                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mDiagnosis:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                                                    \r\n\r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mReason\u001b[0m: The container image \u001b[1;36;40mmyapp:doesnt-exist\u001b[0m does not exist in any accessible registry.                                                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mWhy it's happening\u001b[0m: The pod is trying to use an image that cannot be found, likely due to a typo or incorrect image name.                                                                  \r\n\u001b[1m • \u001b[0m\u001b[1mNext step\u001b[0m: Verify the correct image name and ensure it exists in the specified registry. Update the deployment configuration with the correct image name.                                  \r\n\r\n\u001b[1;35mConclusion:\u001b[0m                                                                                                                                                                                   \r\n\r\nThe pod is not starting because of an invalid container image. Correct the image name in the deployment configuration and redeploy the application.                                           \r\n"]
